<h1 class="postingtitle">
    <span class="postingtitletext">
<span class="price">$2,900</span> <span class="housing">/ 3br - 1100ft<sup>2</sup> - </span><span id="titletextonly">3br, 1bth Bright Home in Secaucus, Close to NYC</span><small> (Secaucus)</small>    </span>
</h1>
<section class="userbody">
    

    <div class="mapAndAttrs">
<div class="mapbox">
    <div id="map" class="viewposting" data-latitude="40.791000" data-longitude="-74.063400" data-accuracy="22"></div>
    
    
</div>

    <p class="attrgroup">



            <span class="shared-line-bubble"><b>3BR</b> / <b>1Ba</b></span>




             <span class="shared-line-bubble"><b>1100</b>ft<sup>2</sup></span>




            <span class="housing_movein_now property_date shared-line-bubble" data-date="2022-09-01" data-today_msg="available now">available sep 1</span>

    </p>
    <p class="attrgroup">



            <span>air conditioning</span>
            <br>




            <span>furnished</span>
            <br>




            <span>apartment</span>
            <br>




            <span>laundry on site</span>
            <br>




            <span>no smoking</span>
            <br>




            <span>street parking</span>
            <br>




            <span>rent period: <b>monthly</b></span>
            <br>

    </p>
    </div>

    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="https://newjersey.craigslist.org/apa/d/secaucus-3br-1bth-bright-home-in/7511061424.html"></div>
        </div>
I bought this home in 2020 and am planning to do a lot of traveling and working on a new business project upstate. It's a lot of space for just me so I'm renting the whole home but I will be living on the first floor of the home part-time which has a completely separate entrance and living space (there will be no contact). I am a mostly vegan (chicken &amp; fish occasionally) rock climber and lover of the outdoors. I spend a lot of time at my partner's home or traveling to climb. I'm extremely quiet and respectful of noise so I'm looking for the perfect couple or family for this unique living space. NO ROOMMATES!<br>
<br>
This is a three bedroom, 1 bath home with a separate small office nook near the living room. Rent is $2900 and includes one driveway parking spot, water and internet. Tenant responsible for gas/electric. and all utilities. <br>
<br>
This home has lots of natural light in the living area. There is a two-year old private washer/dryer. <br>
<br>
There is a very clean park for kids directly behind the house. And Secaucus is one of the top rated locations for public schools. Check out niche.com. There are tennis and basketball courts nearby.<br>
<br>
The home comes with a built-in 75" television and two bookshelves in the living room. Other furniture may be included upon request. <br>
<br>
No pets allowed! No smoking inside of the home. There are steps to get to the 2nd floor but they are not exposed to the living space in case you have small children. <br>
<br>
I have a plot at the community garden (organic) that you're welcome to harvest from, especially if you help out with summer waterings when I'm traveling. There is an awesome community center with an outdoor waterpark in the summer and indoor gym, track and lap pool.<br>
<br>
The home is a 15-minute drive to NYC (not during rush hour), 12-minute train ride from Secaucus Junction. I typically bike to the train station (10 mins or less) but you can also walk there in about 20-25 minutes. There is also a bus nearby that goes to Port Authority. There is also a parking lot at Secaucus Junction that is only a 4-5 min drive from the home.<br>
<br>
Looking for a small family seeking a long-term secure home. The access is keyless using smart locks and there are keys to lock the main door of the apartment within the home.<br>
<br>
Credit/Background check $50 and interview required! Move-in September 1 or later. Not looking to rush someone here. Looking for the right people to live in a home I love. Must supply 1st month and 1 month security deposit to move in.<br>
<br>
Showings by appointment only!<br>
    </section>

